WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.491 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.491 --> 00:00:11.331 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.331 --> 00:00:12.530 align:middle line:84%
RADIO ANNOUNCER:
This is [INAUDIBLE]

00:00:12.530 --> 00:00:15.780 align:middle line:84%
102.5 Los Angeles, coming at
you live at the top of the hour.

00:00:15.780 --> 00:00:17.500 align:middle line:84%
If you are on the
405 southbounds,

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:18.760 align:middle line:90%
you are not going to be happy.

00:00:18.760 --> 00:00:20.330 align:middle line:84%
A collision at Century
has the two right lanes

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:23.060 align:middle line:84%
blocked and traffic backed to
the Wilshire Boulevard on-ramp.

00:00:23.060 --> 00:00:25.350 align:middle line:84%
Authorities are working
on clearing the lanes.

00:00:25.350 --> 00:00:26.978 align:middle line:90%
But in the meantime--

00:00:26.978 --> 00:00:30.850 align:middle line:90%
[CAR HORNS]

00:00:30.850 --> 00:00:32.087 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.087 --> 00:00:32.786 align:middle line:90%
Shit.

00:00:32.786 --> 00:00:36.340 align:middle line:90%


00:00:36.340 --> 00:00:39.110 align:middle line:84%
I can't recall the exact
moment when I realized

00:00:39.110 --> 00:00:40.550 align:middle line:90%
my life was out of control.

00:00:40.550 --> 00:00:41.730 align:middle line:90%
[MOAN]

00:00:41.730 --> 00:00:46.360 align:middle line:84%
I had survived a dysfunctional
childhood, two divorces,

00:00:46.360 --> 00:00:50.010 align:middle line:84%
single parenthood, the
Northridge earthquake,

00:00:50.010 --> 00:00:52.130 align:middle line:84%
dealt with my mother's
Alzheimer's disease,

00:00:52.130 --> 00:00:56.130 align:middle line:84%
and my hair had finally grown
back after a year of chemo.

00:00:56.130 --> 00:00:59.640 align:middle line:84%
But what was about to unfold
would be the catalyst that

00:00:59.640 --> 00:01:02.340 align:middle line:84%
would lead me on a
journey of self-discovery,

00:01:02.340 --> 00:01:04.769 align:middle line:84%
empowerment, and a
reconnection to the whole.

00:01:04.769 --> 00:01:06.285 align:middle line:84%
(SCREAMING) Oh,
come on, god dammit!

00:01:06.285 --> 00:01:06.985 align:middle line:90%
Move!

00:01:06.985 --> 00:01:09.916 align:middle line:90%


00:01:09.916 --> 00:01:10.908 align:middle line:90%
Pearl, you are late.

00:01:10.908 --> 00:01:11.744 align:middle line:90%
I know, I know.

00:01:11.744 --> 00:01:12.710 align:middle line:10%
My cell phone wouldn't work--

00:01:12.710 --> 00:01:14.082 align:middle line:10%
-John wants you to call him.
-OK.

00:01:14.082 --> 00:01:15.715 align:middle line:10%
[INAUDIBLE].
This can wait.

00:01:15.715 --> 00:01:17.590 align:middle line:90%
Mike wants that file ASAP.

00:01:17.590 --> 00:01:20.796 align:middle line:90%


00:01:20.796 --> 00:01:24.268 align:middle line:90%
[PHONE RINGING]

00:01:24.268 --> 00:01:25.260 align:middle line:90%


00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:26.340 align:middle line:90%
You're late, Ms. Weaver.

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:27.620 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry, traffic.

00:01:27.620 --> 00:01:29.440 align:middle line:84%
That's why they
invented cell phones.

00:01:29.440 --> 00:01:30.270 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:01:30.270 --> 00:01:32.990 align:middle line:84%
The notes on the joint
venture for the Soderburg deal.

00:01:32.990 --> 00:01:35.050 align:middle line:84%
I told you last night
to have them printed

00:01:35.050 --> 00:01:36.420 align:middle line:90%
out for this morning's meeting.

00:01:36.420 --> 00:01:38.570 align:middle line:84%
And I gave you specific
instructions to leave

00:01:38.570 --> 00:01:40.550 align:middle line:90%
them on my desk for review.

00:01:40.550 --> 00:01:42.250 align:middle line:90%
Well, they weren't there.

00:01:42.250 --> 00:01:44.890 align:middle line:84%
They're not on my computer,
and the originals are missing.

00:01:44.890 --> 00:01:46.377 align:middle line:90%
So where the hell are they, Pam?

00:01:46.377 --> 00:01:47.610 align:middle line:84%
Did you delete them
from my computer?

00:01:47.610 --> 00:01:49.443 align:middle line:84%
No of course I didn't delete
them from your computer--

00:01:49.443 --> 00:01:50.630 align:middle line:84%
-I don't want to hear it.
-Look--

00:01:50.630 --> 00:01:51.430 align:middle line:90%
You're not fooling me--

00:01:51.430 --> 00:01:52.200 align:middle line:90%
Calm down.

00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:52.900 align:middle line:90%
I will--

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:54.925 align:middle line:90%
Don't condescend me!

00:01:54.925 --> 00:01:57.060 align:middle line:84%
I'll print out another
one for the meeting, OK?

00:01:57.060 --> 00:02:00.090 align:middle line:90%


00:02:00.090 --> 00:02:01.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, you certainly
aren't behaving

00:02:01.290 --> 00:02:03.550 align:middle line:90%
like a patriotic-- oh, my God.

00:02:03.550 --> 00:02:05.873 align:middle line:84%
Saddam has had plenty of time to
conduct those weapons searches.

00:02:05.873 --> 00:02:07.273 align:middle line:84%
OFFICE WORKER: Yeah,
but what if there are

00:02:07.273 --> 00:02:08.306 align:middle line:90%
no weapons of mass destruction?

00:02:08.306 --> 00:02:10.150 align:middle line:84%
Why start a whole military
conflict on something

00:02:10.150 --> 00:02:11.120 align:middle line:90%
that's not even definite?

00:02:11.120 --> 00:02:12.653 align:middle line:84%
So you know more than
the president, I guess?

00:02:12.653 --> 00:02:14.067 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's not saying much.

00:02:14.067 --> 00:02:15.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, then just let
him ask where you're--

00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:16.680 align:middle line:90%
Guys, guys, guys.

00:02:16.680 --> 00:02:20.140 align:middle line:84%
I can't hear, OK?
Hello, yes?

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:23.350 align:middle line:90%


00:02:23.350 --> 00:02:24.100 align:middle line:90%
Yes, hello?

00:02:24.100 --> 00:02:30.368 align:middle line:90%


00:02:30.368 --> 00:02:31.067 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:02:31.067 --> 00:02:35.570 align:middle line:90%


00:02:35.570 --> 00:02:37.690 align:middle line:84%
Did you locate
those papers yet?

00:02:37.690 --> 00:02:39.530 align:middle line:90%
Mike, it's my daughter.

00:02:39.530 --> 00:02:40.740 align:middle line:90%
She's been arrested.

00:02:40.740 --> 00:02:42.440 align:middle line:84%
It's not like she's
going anywhere.

00:02:42.440 --> 00:02:44.500 align:middle line:84%
I need those papers
before 11:00.

00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:47.150 align:middle line:10%
They got my grandson.

00:02:47.150 --> 00:02:49.875 align:middle line:84%
You walk out now, and you
will suffer the consequences.

00:02:49.875 --> 00:02:58.380 align:middle line:90%


00:02:58.380 --> 00:02:59.440 align:middle line:10%
Right where I left it.

00:02:59.440 --> 00:03:03.010 align:middle line:90%


00:03:03.010 --> 00:03:05.670 align:middle line:84%
A few weeks before, I had
received a call in the middle

00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:07.170 align:middle line:84%
of the night from
an unknown caller,

00:03:07.170 --> 00:03:08.615 align:middle line:84%
telling me my
daughter had broken

00:03:08.615 --> 00:03:12.850 align:middle line:84%
into my house, stolen checks,
credit cards, and my identity.

00:03:12.850 --> 00:03:16.020 align:middle line:84%
She was held up in a motel
across town with my grandson,

00:03:16.020 --> 00:03:18.800 align:middle line:84%
intending on leaving the
state the next morning.

00:03:18.800 --> 00:03:20.770 align:middle line:84%
I called the police, but
she had already checked

00:03:20.770 --> 00:03:22.760 align:middle line:90%
out by the time they arrived.

00:03:22.760 --> 00:03:24.070 align:middle line:84%
They finally caught
up with her when

00:03:24.070 --> 00:03:26.520 align:middle line:84%
she went to retrieve her
belongings from a storage shed

00:03:26.520 --> 00:03:29.945 align:middle line:84%
and had paid the fees
with a stolen check.

00:03:29.945 --> 00:03:32.300 align:middle line:90%
Insufficient evidence.

00:03:32.300 --> 00:03:35.630 align:middle line:84%
That's what the judge
said, so they released her.

00:03:35.630 --> 00:03:38.710 align:middle line:84%
Two years passed, and her
drug use and criminal behavior

00:03:38.710 --> 00:03:40.260 align:middle line:90%
increased.

00:03:40.260 --> 00:03:43.900 align:middle line:84%
She also now had two more
children, and I was to learn,

00:03:43.900 --> 00:03:46.330 align:middle line:90%
pregnant with her fourth baby.

00:03:46.330 --> 00:03:50.670 align:middle line:84%
ARIANA: Mom, I
know I've told you

00:03:50.670 --> 00:03:55.272 align:middle line:84%
before about how I'm
not-- I'm not doing drugs,

00:03:55.272 --> 00:03:57.380 align:middle line:90%
and that I'm fine.

00:03:57.380 --> 00:04:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:01.725 align:middle line:90%
But I'm not.

00:04:01.725 --> 00:04:04.750 align:middle line:90%


00:04:04.750 --> 00:04:08.690 align:middle line:84%
PAM: All the self-help groups
and books preached tough love.

00:04:08.690 --> 00:04:10.676 align:middle line:90%
Don't give into the con.

00:04:10.676 --> 00:04:12.710 align:middle line:90%
I mean, she was talented.

00:04:12.710 --> 00:04:16.160 align:middle line:84%
She got-- she was
picked out of 1,500 kids

00:04:16.160 --> 00:04:19.910 align:middle line:84%
to be in Hollywood High School,
a dream that I had growing up.

00:04:19.910 --> 00:04:22.360 align:middle line:84%
And she was good at
it, and she blew it.

00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:23.750 align:middle line:84%
Instead of going to
school, she would

00:04:23.750 --> 00:04:25.470 align:middle line:84%
be hanging out with
all the druggies

00:04:25.470 --> 00:04:27.290 align:middle line:90%
on Hollywood Boulevard.

00:04:27.290 --> 00:04:28.985 align:middle line:84%
She knew them by first name.
No.

00:04:28.985 --> 00:04:29.973 align:middle line:90%
The answer's no.

00:04:29.973 --> 00:04:30.820 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:04:30.820 --> 00:04:33.800 align:middle line:84%
I buried my mother, and
you break into my house.

00:04:33.800 --> 00:04:37.862 align:middle line:84%
How in the world do you
expect me to trust you?

00:04:37.862 --> 00:04:39.314 align:middle line:90%
I need your help.

00:04:39.314 --> 00:04:42.710 align:middle line:90%


00:04:42.710 --> 00:04:46.611 align:middle line:84%
PAM: She burned
me so many times.

00:04:46.611 --> 00:04:47.310 align:middle line:90%
Then what the f--

00:04:47.310 --> 00:04:52.700 align:middle line:90%


00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:54.170 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry.
No.

00:04:54.170 --> 00:04:57.130 align:middle line:90%


00:04:57.130 --> 00:04:59.030 align:middle line:90%
You're my mother.

00:04:59.030 --> 00:05:00.540 align:middle line:90%
You're my flesh and blood!

00:05:00.540 --> 00:05:03.250 align:middle line:90%
Only when it's convenient.

00:05:03.250 --> 00:05:05.810 align:middle line:84%
Only when it's convenient.
-Please.

00:05:05.810 --> 00:05:07.720 align:middle line:90%
I need help, Mom.

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:10.910 align:middle line:90%


00:05:10.910 --> 00:05:13.360 align:middle line:84%
PAM: Devin, don't
draw on the wall.

00:05:13.360 --> 00:05:14.300 align:middle line:90%
Bring that down.

00:05:14.300 --> 00:05:18.550 align:middle line:84%
You can play-- you can use it
on the-- on the-- the, um-- God,

00:05:18.550 --> 00:05:19.695 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
I'm going to do.

00:05:19.695 --> 00:05:21.016 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the-- the
authorities tell me

00:05:21.016 --> 00:05:22.215 align:middle line:84%
if I don't take
custody of the kids,

00:05:22.215 --> 00:05:25.226 align:middle line:84%
they're going to put
them in foster care.

00:05:25.226 --> 00:05:25.925 align:middle line:90%
And my-- my job.

00:05:25.925 --> 00:05:27.424 align:middle line:84%
I mean, who's going to
take care of the kids?

00:05:27.424 --> 00:05:30.668 align:middle line:90%
My house is too small.

00:05:30.668 --> 00:05:32.590 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, you know, my-- my boss?

00:05:32.590 --> 00:05:34.690 align:middle line:84%
He wouldn't even grant me
time off when I was-- when

00:05:34.690 --> 00:05:36.000 align:middle line:90%
my mother was dying, you know?

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:39.200 align:middle line:84%
And I had to wait an entire
week to bury her on a weekend.

00:05:39.200 --> 00:05:40.535 align:middle line:90%
[KIDS SHRIEKING]

00:05:40.535 --> 00:05:41.870 align:middle line:90%
My God, what do I do?

00:05:41.870 --> 00:05:42.760 align:middle line:90%
No, Devin.

00:05:42.760 --> 00:05:43.988 align:middle line:90%
Put that away.

00:05:43.988 --> 00:05:46.480 align:middle line:84%
I think it's admirable that
you're taking all this on, Pam,

00:05:46.480 --> 00:05:47.722 align:middle line:90%
but I've got to tell you.

00:05:47.722 --> 00:05:52.600 align:middle line:84%
Our relationship did not include
taking care of all these kids.

00:05:52.600 --> 00:05:55.430 align:middle line:90%
It's your decision.

00:05:55.430 --> 00:05:58.640 align:middle line:90%
What are you saying?

00:05:58.640 --> 00:06:00.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm saying kids--
[CLUNK]

00:06:00.140 --> 00:06:01.360 align:middle line:90%
[BABY TALK]

00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:04.714 align:middle line:84%
Kids were never a
part of the package.

00:06:04.714 --> 00:06:06.172 align:middle line:90%
[BABY TALK]

00:06:06.172 --> 00:06:07.630 align:middle line:90%
CHILD: Where's John going?

00:06:07.630 --> 00:06:10.546 align:middle line:84%
Where's John--
where's John going?

00:06:10.546 --> 00:06:12.980 align:middle line:90%
I don't know, honey.

00:06:12.980 --> 00:06:14.210 align:middle line:90%
OK, OK.

00:06:14.210 --> 00:06:17.750 align:middle line:84%
And it was very
difficult to see her.

00:06:17.750 --> 00:06:21.910 align:middle line:84%
And she came up to
me and she said,

00:06:21.910 --> 00:06:28.780 align:middle line:84%
mom, it wasn't your fault. I
had the dream everybody wanted.

00:06:28.780 --> 00:06:29.925 align:middle line:90%
I had a job.

00:06:29.925 --> 00:06:32.620 align:middle line:90%


00:06:32.620 --> 00:06:36.730 align:middle line:84%
I had moved to California
for my career as an actress.

00:06:36.730 --> 00:06:39.950 align:middle line:84%
I had my own house
in California,

00:06:39.950 --> 00:06:43.084 align:middle line:90%
and I got it on my own.

00:06:43.084 --> 00:06:44.497 align:middle line:90%
And I was selling it.

00:06:44.497 --> 00:06:47.330 align:middle line:90%


00:06:47.330 --> 00:06:49.550 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:06:49.550 --> 00:06:52.810 align:middle line:84%
Because what if my
daughter didn't make it

00:06:52.810 --> 00:06:55.000 align:middle line:90%
and I did have to take the kids?

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.820 align:middle line:90%
I had no room.

00:06:57.820 --> 00:06:59.010 align:middle line:90%
So I bought a bigger house.

00:06:59.010 --> 00:07:03.730 align:middle line:90%


00:07:03.730 --> 00:07:04.765 align:middle line:90%
And I had no job.

00:07:04.765 --> 00:07:09.170 align:middle line:90%


00:07:09.170 --> 00:07:11.580 align:middle line:90%
And I know nobody in Texas.

00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:21.680 align:middle line:90%


00:07:21.680 --> 00:07:22.890 align:middle line:90%
But it was a leap of faith.

00:07:22.890 --> 00:07:26.540 align:middle line:90%


00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:31.280 align:middle line:84%
I hate the fact that my daughter
and grandkids are living here

00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:33.410 align:middle line:84%
with a bunch of
druggies and bums,

00:07:33.410 --> 00:07:38.180 align:middle line:84%
but it's still better than
Skid Row or the weekly moves

00:07:38.180 --> 00:07:40.360 align:middle line:84%
from one flea bag
hotel to the other.

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:42.650 align:middle line:84%
And the church did agree
to give her and the kids

00:07:42.650 --> 00:07:46.510 align:middle line:84%
a place to stay while she
completed the necessary rehab

00:07:46.510 --> 00:07:49.315 align:middle line:84%
programs to regain
custody of her kids

00:07:49.315 --> 00:07:53.030 align:middle line:84%
that she lost after
they had been removed

00:07:53.030 --> 00:07:56.520 align:middle line:84%
by the state when
she failed to return

00:07:56.520 --> 00:07:59.270 align:middle line:90%
after a night of partying.

00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:03.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm happy that she's finally
getting her life together.

00:08:03.950 --> 00:08:08.480 align:middle line:84%
But I also fear that
history will repeat itself.

00:08:08.480 --> 00:08:11.115 align:middle line:84%
That was one of the reasons
why I bought property in Texas.

00:08:11.115 --> 00:08:16.520 align:middle line:90%


00:08:16.520 --> 00:08:22.320 align:middle line:84%
And the state told me
that she did everything

00:08:22.320 --> 00:08:25.210 align:middle line:90%
they required of her.

00:08:25.210 --> 00:08:28.800 align:middle line:90%
And she got her kids back.

00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:33.600 align:middle line:84%
But she's still staying in
this roach-infested place.

00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:36.287 align:middle line:90%
[CAR HORNS]

00:08:36.287 --> 00:09:04.530 align:middle line:90%


00:09:04.530 --> 00:09:05.229 align:middle line:90%
Hi.

00:09:05.229 --> 00:09:12.730 align:middle line:90%


00:09:12.730 --> 00:09:18.240 align:middle line:84%
PAM: Two months after I left,
the minister himself was caught

00:09:18.240 --> 00:09:21.310 align:middle line:90%
shooting up in a bathroom.

00:09:21.310 --> 00:09:26.440 align:middle line:84%
He lost the minister position
that he had at the church,

00:09:26.440 --> 00:09:28.410 align:middle line:84%
and the church has
since been closed down.

00:09:28.410 --> 00:09:33.750 align:middle line:90%


00:09:33.750 --> 00:09:41.260 align:middle line:84%
Guilt. Guilt at the fact
that I wasn't a good mom,

00:09:41.260 --> 00:09:43.920 align:middle line:90%
that I was running away.

00:09:43.920 --> 00:09:45.880 align:middle line:84%
You can't take
anymore, you chuck it

00:09:45.880 --> 00:09:49.155 align:middle line:90%
up and just get out of there.

00:09:49.155 --> 00:09:53.311 align:middle line:84%
But I saw that as my own
salvation, because if I stayed,

00:09:53.311 --> 00:09:56.120 align:middle line:84%
I was going to go
crazy, and I didn't know

00:09:56.120 --> 00:09:57.247 align:middle line:90%
what was going to happen next.

00:09:57.247 --> 00:10:06.030 align:middle line:90%


00:10:06.030 --> 00:10:08.265 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to abandon
me like dad did, are you?

00:10:08.265 --> 00:10:21.960 align:middle line:90%


00:10:21.960 --> 00:10:25.150 align:middle line:90%
I will always be your mom.

00:10:25.150 --> 00:10:26.723 align:middle line:84%
I'm very proud of you.
-All right.

00:10:26.723 --> 00:10:35.404 align:middle line:90%


00:10:35.404 --> 00:10:37.373 align:middle line:90%
I'll call you, OK?

00:10:37.373 --> 00:10:39.297 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:39.297 --> 00:10:43.145 align:middle line:90%
[AIRPLANE ENGINES]

00:10:43.145 --> 00:11:04.350 align:middle line:90%


00:11:04.350 --> 00:11:06.365 align:middle line:90%
It's yours.

00:11:06.365 --> 00:11:10.780 align:middle line:84%
You can do with
it what you want.

00:11:10.780 --> 00:11:11.479 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:11:11.479 --> 00:11:21.420 align:middle line:90%


00:11:21.420 --> 00:11:25.110 align:middle line:84%
PAM: And when she asked me
that, about, are you going

00:11:25.110 --> 00:11:26.355 align:middle line:84%
to abandon me, I
kept telling her,

00:11:26.355 --> 00:11:28.640 align:middle line:84%
I said, I'm just
a phone call away.

00:11:28.640 --> 00:11:31.180 align:middle line:90%
It's not a big deal, you know?

00:11:31.180 --> 00:11:32.805 align:middle line:90%
I'm not abandoning you.

00:11:32.805 --> 00:11:36.220 align:middle line:84%
But when I got on the
plane, that's exactly what

00:11:36.220 --> 00:11:38.230 align:middle line:90%
I felt I was doing.

00:11:38.230 --> 00:11:40.500 align:middle line:84%
And I was running away
from my daughter's problems

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:43.070 align:middle line:90%
that I couldn't handle anymore.

00:11:43.070 --> 00:11:46.760 align:middle line:84%
And I always thought I'd be
stuck with raising up four

00:11:46.760 --> 00:11:49.926 align:middle line:90%
babies under the age of six.

00:11:49.926 --> 00:11:51.170 align:middle line:90%
60 years old.

00:11:51.170 --> 00:11:53.810 align:middle line:90%


00:11:53.810 --> 00:11:54.590 align:middle line:90%
In a few years.

00:11:54.590 --> 00:12:02.050 align:middle line:90%


00:12:02.050 --> 00:12:05.000 align:middle line:90%
My new life in Austin.

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:13.584 align:middle line:84%
New home, new car, no
job, no health insurance.

00:12:13.584 --> 00:12:15.072 align:middle line:90%
Just a leap of faith.

00:12:15.072 --> 00:12:18.050 align:middle line:90%


00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:20.290 align:middle line:84%
My realtor invited me
to a drumming session

00:12:20.290 --> 00:12:21.655 align:middle line:84%
where I met several
women who asked

00:12:21.655 --> 00:12:25.088 align:middle line:84%
me to join them on the
trip to hike Machu Picchu.

00:12:25.088 --> 00:12:26.720 align:middle line:90%
The catch?

00:12:26.720 --> 00:12:29.600 align:middle line:90%
They were leaving in four days.

00:12:29.600 --> 00:12:30.780 align:middle line:90%
It was that leap of faith again.

00:12:30.780 --> 00:12:35.460 align:middle line:90%


00:12:35.460 --> 00:12:38.000 align:middle line:84%
I was able to synchronize
my travel schedule

00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:40.040 align:middle line:84%
with the other girls,
even an the zenith hour

00:12:40.040 --> 00:12:41.750 align:middle line:90%
before departure.

00:12:41.750 --> 00:12:44.070 align:middle line:90%
Amazing in itself.

00:12:44.070 --> 00:12:46.310 align:middle line:84%
I learned that most of the
people I'm about to meet

00:12:46.310 --> 00:12:48.840 align:middle line:84%
on this journey are
healers of sorts,

00:12:48.840 --> 00:12:54.440 align:middle line:84%
specializing in Reiki, some
sort of hands-on energy healing.

00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:56.795 align:middle line:84%
But it was my first
vacation in years,

00:12:56.795 --> 00:13:00.890 align:middle line:84%
and I was really looking forward
to relaxation and a reprieve

00:13:00.890 --> 00:13:04.410 align:middle line:90%
from my hectic life in LA.

00:13:04.410 --> 00:13:07.280 align:middle line:84%
We had a several hour
layover at the Lima airport

00:13:07.280 --> 00:13:10.300 align:middle line:84%
before connecting with
our flight to Cusco.

00:13:10.300 --> 00:13:14.510 align:middle line:84%
Upon our arrival, Edemid
Rossi, a Brazilian healer,

00:13:14.510 --> 00:13:16.740 align:middle line:90%
and our host greet us.

00:13:16.740 --> 00:13:19.810 align:middle line:10%
After formal introductions, we
grab some coffee at the food

00:13:19.810 --> 00:13:24.767 align:middle line:10%
lounge and Edemir suddenly, in
mid conversation turns to me

00:13:24.767 --> 00:13:26.290 align:middle line:10%
and says--

00:13:26.290 --> 00:13:30.320 align:middle line:10%
EDEMIR: You are from
the Atlantean lineage.

00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:37.620 align:middle line:10%
Your job on this journey is
to connect with with angels.

00:13:37.620 --> 00:13:41.040 align:middle line:84%
You are like a branch
that has no roots,

00:13:41.040 --> 00:13:44.580 align:middle line:90%
waving wildly in the wind.

00:13:44.580 --> 00:13:47.120 align:middle line:84%
Your life is going to
change dramatically.

00:13:47.120 --> 00:13:54.110 align:middle line:90%


00:13:54.110 --> 00:13:56.920 align:middle line:90%
PAM: I'm from Atlantis?

00:13:56.920 --> 00:13:58.760 align:middle line:84%
Our discussions at
the Lima airport

00:13:58.760 --> 00:14:02.670 align:middle line:84%
were strange enough as it
was, but when I walked off

00:14:02.670 --> 00:14:06.620 align:middle line:84%
that plane in
Cusco, I had no idea

00:14:06.620 --> 00:14:10.130 align:middle line:90%
what was still ahead for me.

00:14:10.130 --> 00:14:15.010 align:middle line:10%
As I grabbed my luggage, I
heard someone call my name.

00:14:15.010 --> 00:14:18.050 align:middle line:90%
It was Puma, a local shaman.

00:14:18.050 --> 00:14:22.490 align:middle line:84%
He startled me as he hugged me
and whispered in my ear, ah.

00:14:22.490 --> 00:14:24.820 align:middle line:90%
You're the warrior.

00:14:24.820 --> 00:14:27.435 align:middle line:84%
He said, that funny feeling
that you're experiencing?

00:14:27.435 --> 00:14:30.870 align:middle line:84%
It's not jet lag
or a lack of sleep,

00:14:30.870 --> 00:14:34.460 align:middle line:84%
but your soul recognizing
a coming home.

00:14:34.460 --> 00:14:38.930 align:middle line:84%
You've been here before, and
Cusco is welcoming you back.

00:14:38.930 --> 00:14:42.900 align:middle line:84%
And just as suddenly as he
appeared, Puma was gone.

00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:45.380 align:middle line:84%
We piled into a van and headed
to our hotel in Ollantaytambo.

00:14:45.380 --> 00:14:50.210 align:middle line:90%


00:14:50.210 --> 00:14:53.660 align:middle line:84%
The next morning, Edemir and
I decided to take a short hike

00:14:53.660 --> 00:14:55.080 align:middle line:90%
to the ruins before breakfast.

00:14:55.080 --> 00:15:05.300 align:middle line:90%


00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:07.490 align:middle line:84%
Our destination was a little
further up the mountain

00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:14.450 align:middle line:84%
than we had anticipated, so we
took a shortcut across a river.

00:15:14.450 --> 00:15:17.740 align:middle line:90%
[SCREAM]

00:15:17.740 --> 00:15:19.630 align:middle line:90%


00:15:19.630 --> 00:15:22.840 align:middle line:10%
Edemir immediately applied
Reiki, but by the time

00:15:22.840 --> 00:15:28.140 align:middle line:10%
we hiked back to town some
eight miles, by leg gave out.

00:15:28.140 --> 00:15:31.060 align:middle line:84%
As I limped into the
square, Jennifer,

00:15:31.060 --> 00:15:33.650 align:middle line:84%
the owner of a local
restaurant, coaxed me inside.

00:15:33.650 --> 00:15:37.160 align:middle line:84%
Taking off my shoes,
she examined my injury

00:15:37.160 --> 00:15:39.830 align:middle line:90%
and said she could help.

00:15:39.830 --> 00:15:43.230 align:middle line:84%
But upon closer
examination, she noticed

00:15:43.230 --> 00:15:45.310 align:middle line:84%
something was very
wrong, and asked

00:15:45.310 --> 00:15:47.960 align:middle line:90%
permission to call in a shaman.

00:15:47.960 --> 00:15:50.150 align:middle line:90%
It was Puma.

00:15:50.150 --> 00:15:52.550 align:middle line:10%
I will catch up with you!

00:15:52.550 --> 00:15:56.380 align:middle line:84%
PAM: The tendons in my foot
had separated from the bone.

00:15:56.380 --> 00:15:59.750 align:middle line:84%
After manipulation, a
ritual bath of human urine

00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:02.950 align:middle line:84%
and wrapping my foot and
ankle in a cast of herbs,

00:16:02.950 --> 00:16:06.230 align:middle line:90%
Puma prayed for intervention.

00:16:06.230 --> 00:16:09.880 align:middle line:84%
My dream of hiking the
Inca Trail was dashed.

00:16:09.880 --> 00:16:13.700 align:middle line:84%
The tour would
continue without me.

00:16:13.700 --> 00:16:17.710 align:middle line:84%
By the third day, and
sensing my depression,

00:16:17.710 --> 00:16:22.810 align:middle line:84%
our host, Joaquin, located the
sole pair of crutches in town.

00:16:22.810 --> 00:16:25.350 align:middle line:90%
I was now mobile.

00:16:25.350 --> 00:16:28.220 align:middle line:84%
Puma arranged for me to
join him on horseback

00:16:28.220 --> 00:16:30.590 align:middle line:84%
to a campout at the Glacier
for a native celebration.

00:16:30.590 --> 00:16:36.420 align:middle line:90%


00:16:36.420 --> 00:16:39.710 align:middle line:84%
In preparation for the trip,
we stopped at Puma's hometown

00:16:39.710 --> 00:16:41.480 align:middle line:90%
of Chinchero.

00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:44.750 align:middle line:84%
I learned that at age six,
Puma was struck by lightning

00:16:44.750 --> 00:16:46.990 align:middle line:90%
while swimming in a river.

00:16:46.990 --> 00:16:49.160 align:middle line:84%
This is an omen in
Andean tradition,

00:16:49.160 --> 00:16:52.380 align:middle line:84%
that an individual has
been chosen by God to walk

00:16:52.380 --> 00:16:54.560 align:middle line:90%
the path of the shamans.

00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:57.230 align:middle line:84%
After a cup of coca
tea, Puma lead me

00:16:57.230 --> 00:17:00.300 align:middle line:84%
to the site of his initiation
where his official training

00:17:00.300 --> 00:17:04.339 align:middle line:84%
began, tutored by his
grandfather, a great medicine

00:17:04.339 --> 00:17:07.250 align:middle line:90%
man and healer in his own right.

00:17:07.250 --> 00:17:14.510 align:middle line:10%
In Chinchero, main altars
were built always facing west.

00:17:14.510 --> 00:17:16.560 align:middle line:84%
And like many of the
sites in this place,

00:17:16.560 --> 00:17:19.970 align:middle line:84%
the reason why they did that
is because we are acknowledging

00:17:19.970 --> 00:17:22.349 align:middle line:90%
the path of our ancestors.

00:17:22.349 --> 00:17:24.940 align:middle line:84%
And that's why this
whole temple over here

00:17:24.940 --> 00:17:32.610 align:middle line:84%
was only for the eternal
bodies of mummified masters.

00:17:32.610 --> 00:17:35.260 align:middle line:84%
Some of them were
prophets, and were

00:17:35.260 --> 00:17:43.570 align:middle line:84%
others were leaders, governors,
masters, healers, and priests.

00:17:43.570 --> 00:17:49.240 align:middle line:84%
And because they were of very,
very important service while

00:17:49.240 --> 00:17:51.060 align:middle line:84%
in their physical
temple, they had

00:17:51.060 --> 00:17:52.610 align:middle line:90%
the privilege to be mummified.

00:17:52.610 --> 00:17:57.180 align:middle line:84%
And this is where
their temple was.

00:17:57.180 --> 00:18:03.080 align:middle line:84%
And in there, in this place
called Pumakaka, which we call

00:18:03.080 --> 00:18:07.870 align:middle line:84%
the rock of the puma, is
these two carved figures

00:18:07.870 --> 00:18:10.900 align:middle line:90%
you can see in the stone.

00:18:10.900 --> 00:18:14.350 align:middle line:84%
The big one over
there is a puma that

00:18:14.350 --> 00:18:20.710 align:middle line:84%
perhaps was looking towards
south or towards this side.

00:18:20.710 --> 00:18:26.980 align:middle line:84%
But when the Spaniards found
it, they cut the head off,

00:18:26.980 --> 00:18:30.490 align:middle line:84%
destroying the power
of the Inca people,

00:18:30.490 --> 00:18:32.830 align:middle line:84%
because the puma
represented that.

00:18:32.830 --> 00:18:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And in this huge
platform used to happen

00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:36.900 align:middle line:90%
the most important ceremonies.

00:18:36.900 --> 00:18:42.120 align:middle line:84%
And yet the puma was not facing
towards the ceremonial site,

00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:46.250 align:middle line:84%
but rather is facing this
way where perhaps this is

00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:48.470 align:middle line:84%
the place where
the most important

00:18:48.470 --> 00:18:50.590 align:middle line:90%
spiritual leaders used to come.

00:18:50.590 --> 00:18:54.790 align:middle line:84%
And there were, at the same
time, generals and warriors,

00:18:54.790 --> 00:18:59.980 align:middle line:84%
and they would initiate boys
and girls into being a man

00:18:59.980 --> 00:19:03.960 align:middle line:84%
and a woman, highly
enlightened, self-realized,

00:19:03.960 --> 00:19:06.660 align:middle line:84%
and at this point, they
have already lived,

00:19:06.660 --> 00:19:09.190 align:middle line:84%
they have already
experienced all the emotions.

00:19:09.190 --> 00:19:11.070 align:middle line:84%
They have already
seen everything

00:19:11.070 --> 00:19:14.350 align:middle line:84%
because they are
preparing as they

00:19:14.350 --> 00:19:16.230 align:middle line:90%
are ready to give a new life.

00:19:16.230 --> 00:19:19.190 align:middle line:90%
And yet their age is 13.

00:19:19.190 --> 00:19:21.293 align:middle line:84%
So boys and girls
would be initiated

00:19:21.293 --> 00:19:23.660 align:middle line:90%
here at the age of 13.

00:19:23.660 --> 00:19:27.160 align:middle line:84%
And what is so beautiful
that it still exists here

00:19:27.160 --> 00:19:29.500 align:middle line:84%
as the essence,
that the Spaniards

00:19:29.500 --> 00:19:31.822 align:middle line:90%
didn't find the little figure.

00:19:31.822 --> 00:19:35.000 align:middle line:84%
Or they found it,
they didn't touch it.

00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:38.350 align:middle line:84%
The little figure
is a baby puma.

00:19:38.350 --> 00:19:40.560 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:19:40.560 --> 00:19:45.930 align:middle line:84%
There's the front crossed
legged, the head, the body,

00:19:45.930 --> 00:19:47.850 align:middle line:90%
the back legs, and the tail.

00:19:47.850 --> 00:19:50.740 align:middle line:90%


00:19:50.740 --> 00:19:55.970 align:middle line:84%
The beautiful part about
that is that the baby

00:19:55.970 --> 00:19:58.120 align:middle line:90%
puma is yet to wake up.

00:19:58.120 --> 00:20:02.310 align:middle line:84%
And that's what gives us the
hope in children and in youth

00:20:02.310 --> 00:20:07.090 align:middle line:84%
here in Chinchero, that there
have been an essence left

00:20:07.090 --> 00:20:10.410 align:middle line:84%
for all the children, for all
the young people, for them

00:20:10.410 --> 00:20:14.390 align:middle line:84%
to go-- like perhaps in
the path I went it was

00:20:14.390 --> 00:20:16.580 align:middle line:90%
initiated by this baby puma.

00:20:16.580 --> 00:20:20.400 align:middle line:84%
And I had to wake up
from being asleep.

00:20:20.400 --> 00:20:23.720 align:middle line:84%
So that is why it is
necessary to go to sleep

00:20:23.720 --> 00:20:26.020 align:middle line:90%
in order to wake up, huh?

00:20:26.020 --> 00:20:31.420 align:middle line:84%
And not only that, but while
the destructive energy came,

00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:35.690 align:middle line:84%
the puma was sleeping, and
that was its protection.

00:20:35.690 --> 00:20:37.380 align:middle line:84%
Which is interesting
medicine, no?

00:20:37.380 --> 00:20:39.080 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:20:39.080 --> 00:20:43.010 align:middle line:84%
And the puma in the
Andes as our cosmo vision

00:20:43.010 --> 00:20:45.060 align:middle line:90%
is the power of will.

00:20:45.060 --> 00:20:48.490 align:middle line:84%
And the power of will does
not come from the mind

00:20:48.490 --> 00:20:50.660 align:middle line:90%
as it is usually known.

00:20:50.660 --> 00:20:53.870 align:middle line:84%
The power of will
comes from the heart.

00:20:53.870 --> 00:20:56.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
power of the puma.

00:20:56.060 --> 00:20:58.400 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we
needed to wake up.

00:20:58.400 --> 00:21:01.760 align:middle line:84%
That is why we were
here in this altar.

00:21:01.760 --> 00:21:07.220 align:middle line:84%
And when the power of will,
which moves everything

00:21:07.220 --> 00:21:12.640 align:middle line:84%
in the whole cosmos, wakes
up, and when you realize

00:21:12.640 --> 00:21:17.370 align:middle line:84%
that its root really is the
heart, and it's not your head,

00:21:17.370 --> 00:21:20.570 align:middle line:84%
it's not your limitations,
it's not your fears,

00:21:20.570 --> 00:21:27.980 align:middle line:84%
then I understood that it really
doesn't matter what you do.

00:21:27.980 --> 00:21:30.910 align:middle line:84%
That power of will
is actually cosmic,

00:21:30.910 --> 00:21:33.030 align:middle line:84%
and it will take you
to the directions

00:21:33.030 --> 00:21:34.970 align:middle line:90%
you are meant to arrive.

00:21:34.970 --> 00:21:40.410 align:middle line:84%
That really you might
choose, but you don't decide.

00:21:40.410 --> 00:21:42.300 align:middle line:90%
The cosmos decides.

00:21:42.300 --> 00:21:47.150 align:middle line:84%
And that is perhaps, when it
was decided by the cosmos,

00:21:47.150 --> 00:21:50.870 align:middle line:84%
we needed to wake up
that puma inside us here.

00:21:50.870 --> 00:21:53.910 align:middle line:84%
And that is why this
medicine is the medicine

00:21:53.910 --> 00:21:57.290 align:middle line:84%
for the whole world, especially
for the young people,

00:21:57.290 --> 00:21:58.970 align:middle line:90%
for the children.

00:21:58.970 --> 00:22:02.760 align:middle line:84%
Because they are the
stewards of life.

00:22:02.760 --> 00:22:06.010 align:middle line:84%
They are the
guardians of the path.

00:22:06.010 --> 00:22:09.610 align:middle line:84%
And the elders are not
so much even leaders.

00:22:09.610 --> 00:22:12.830 align:middle line:84%
They are witnesses of
a new life happening,

00:22:12.830 --> 00:22:14.860 align:middle line:90%
and a new life happening again.

00:22:14.860 --> 00:22:17.870 align:middle line:90%
That is why we say there is iny.

00:22:17.870 --> 00:22:22.950 align:middle line:84%
There's a moment when we
look after our children,

00:22:22.950 --> 00:22:27.270 align:middle line:84%
and that moment is so
delicate because we need

00:22:27.270 --> 00:22:30.294 align:middle line:90%
to be guardians of their path.

00:22:30.294 --> 00:22:37.070 align:middle line:84%
And in a thousandth of a second
that changes, and our children

00:22:37.070 --> 00:22:39.880 align:middle line:90%
need to look after us.

00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:41.640 align:middle line:90%
So there is that iny.

00:22:41.640 --> 00:22:44.860 align:middle line:84%
And oftentimes, a
lot of parents take

00:22:44.860 --> 00:22:48.720 align:middle line:84%
for granted their being parents,
and they think they always

00:22:48.720 --> 00:22:51.550 align:middle line:84%
have to look after the
children, and they forget

00:22:51.550 --> 00:22:54.190 align:middle line:90%
to be looked after, you know?

00:22:54.190 --> 00:22:57.220 align:middle line:84%
And there is the iny, there's
the sharing of the love,

00:22:57.220 --> 00:23:00.040 align:middle line:84%
there is the connection
of the family also.

00:23:00.040 --> 00:23:02.900 align:middle line:84%
When in that order,
families separate,

00:23:02.900 --> 00:23:07.010 align:middle line:84%
when that order families
split, in the cosmos

00:23:07.010 --> 00:23:09.685 align:middle line:90%
there's a huge unbalance.

00:23:09.685 --> 00:23:13.820 align:middle line:84%
In the cosmos is created what
we call perhaps scientifically

00:23:13.820 --> 00:23:22.010 align:middle line:84%
a black hole, a portal, so that
it can take all the sorrow, all

00:23:22.010 --> 00:23:25.380 align:middle line:84%
the traumas, all the
fears, all the pain,

00:23:25.380 --> 00:23:31.160 align:middle line:84%
all the emotional
heaviness and transmute it.

00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:34.720 align:middle line:84%
Take it to another
dimension of light, of love.

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:38.570 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, that
process in the microcosmos

00:23:38.570 --> 00:23:40.000 align:middle line:90%
is huge.

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:41.000 align:middle line:90%
It is devastating.

00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:44.350 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes with that process,
it can take whole galaxies.

00:23:44.350 --> 00:23:47.920 align:middle line:84%
It can take whole
planetary systems.

00:23:47.920 --> 00:23:52.880 align:middle line:84%
And that is why
here in Chinchero

00:23:52.880 --> 00:23:59.790 align:middle line:84%
the relationship of family
is so delicate that it is

00:23:59.790 --> 00:24:02.495 align:middle line:90%
so precious, it is so sacred.

00:24:02.495 --> 00:24:04.630 align:middle line:84%
You don't take it for
granted, whether it

00:24:04.630 --> 00:24:07.750 align:middle line:84%
is your partner, your
children, your parents,

00:24:07.750 --> 00:24:08.870 align:middle line:90%
your grandparents.

00:24:08.870 --> 00:24:11.530 align:middle line:84%
You don't take your
family for granted.

00:24:11.530 --> 00:24:19.310 align:middle line:10%
And you are the one who has the
responsibility to not only help

00:24:19.310 --> 00:24:25.970 align:middle line:10%
it heal and guard it, but
also to lead it, to take it

00:24:25.970 --> 00:24:28.260 align:middle line:10%
to a whole different
level of life

00:24:28.260 --> 00:24:34.340 align:middle line:10%
where you go through the process
of emotions through the hurts,

00:24:34.340 --> 00:24:35.750 align:middle line:10%
through the traumas.

00:24:35.750 --> 00:24:39.760 align:middle line:84%
And then to a level
of celebration,

00:24:39.760 --> 00:24:41.790 align:middle line:90%
to a level of sharing.

00:24:41.790 --> 00:24:43.650 align:middle line:90%
But always together.

00:24:43.650 --> 00:24:48.930 align:middle line:84%
And that is what is necessary,
I think, in the world,

00:24:48.930 --> 00:24:50.960 align:middle line:84%
that everybody has
to have a mentor,

00:24:50.960 --> 00:24:53.060 align:middle line:84%
has to have someone
who will tell

00:24:53.060 --> 00:24:55.520 align:middle line:90%
them to the right or the left.

00:24:55.520 --> 00:24:58.560 align:middle line:84%
And in it, my
grandfather would say,

00:24:58.560 --> 00:25:04.370 align:middle line:84%
you have to listen to
yourself first and last.

00:25:04.370 --> 00:25:06.880 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:25:06.880 --> 00:25:10.880 align:middle line:84%
PAM: Puma didn't know about
the situation I left behind.

00:25:10.880 --> 00:25:13.630 align:middle line:84%
I seemed to be
addressing my own fears,

00:25:13.630 --> 00:25:18.660 align:middle line:84%
my guilt. Was I
wrong in leaving?

00:25:18.660 --> 00:25:21.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm supposed to be the
guardian of my daughter's

00:25:21.040 --> 00:25:25.830 align:middle line:90%
path, her mentor, and I ran.

00:25:25.830 --> 00:25:27.530 align:middle line:84%
But then he tells me
that I need to let

00:25:27.530 --> 00:25:30.010 align:middle line:84%
go, like the
nesting bird pushing

00:25:30.010 --> 00:25:32.558 align:middle line:90%
the babies out of the nest.

00:25:32.558 --> 00:25:36.530 align:middle line:84%
I pondered his messages as we
loaded our gear on the horses

00:25:36.530 --> 00:25:38.035 align:middle line:84%
and proceeded to the
top of the glacier.

00:25:38.035 --> 00:25:43.070 align:middle line:90%


00:25:43.070 --> 00:25:46.350 align:middle line:84%
It was dark when we
finally reached the summit.

00:25:46.350 --> 00:25:50.172 align:middle line:84%
I gasped at the
brightness of the stars.

00:25:50.172 --> 00:25:53.140 align:middle line:90%
I'd never seen the Milky Way.

00:25:53.140 --> 00:25:56.590 align:middle line:84%
So close you feel as
though you can almost

00:25:56.590 --> 00:25:59.600 align:middle line:90%
touch it with your fingers.

00:25:59.600 --> 00:26:02.220 align:middle line:84%
Exhausted and shivering
from the cold,

00:26:02.220 --> 00:26:06.350 align:middle line:84%
Puma covered me with a tarp as
the singing and pounding drums

00:26:06.350 --> 00:26:07.635 align:middle line:90%
continued throughout the night.

00:26:07.635 --> 00:26:10.560 align:middle line:90%


00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:14.290 align:middle line:84%
The next morning, I awoke to
see an entire community that

00:26:14.290 --> 00:26:19.250 align:middle line:84%
had gathered on top this
glacier, 16,000 feet above sea

00:26:19.250 --> 00:26:21.950 align:middle line:90%
level in the Sinaqara Valley.

00:26:21.950 --> 00:26:25.690 align:middle line:84%
I'm told that this glacier
has been rapidly disappearing,

00:26:25.690 --> 00:26:29.320 align:middle line:84%
and that just 10 years ago, the
area where we are now camping

00:26:29.320 --> 00:26:33.120 align:middle line:84%
used to be totally
submerged in snow and ice.

00:26:33.120 --> 00:26:36.710 align:middle line:84%
As I shivered from the
cold, I watched these people

00:26:36.710 --> 00:26:39.990 align:middle line:84%
dancing and singing,
most of them barefoot

00:26:39.990 --> 00:26:42.136 align:middle line:90%
or wearing just sandals.

00:26:42.136 --> 00:26:47.310 align:middle line:84%
I was overwhelmed by the
faith of these people.

00:26:47.310 --> 00:26:50.770 align:middle line:84%
Over 100,000 people
come up here every year

00:26:50.770 --> 00:26:53.680 align:middle line:90%
to celebrate Qoillorritti.

00:26:53.680 --> 00:26:55.750 align:middle line:84%
Qoillorritti is an
annual event that

00:26:55.750 --> 00:26:58.490 align:middle line:84%
has been kept in
secret for many years,

00:26:58.490 --> 00:27:02.710 align:middle line:84%
but has its origins dating
back to early Inca times.

00:27:02.710 --> 00:27:04.950 align:middle line:84%
The tradition is to
go up to the glacier

00:27:04.950 --> 00:27:11.700 align:middle line:84%
and gather the ice as new water,
as new life, a new direction.

00:27:11.700 --> 00:27:15.120 align:middle line:84%
These are people who come
from various lifestyles,

00:27:15.120 --> 00:27:18.900 align:middle line:84%
various communities,
far away distances.

00:27:18.900 --> 00:27:21.800 align:middle line:84%
And not just from Peru,
but some journeying

00:27:21.800 --> 00:27:27.520 align:middle line:84%
all the way from North
America, Europe, Asia.

00:27:27.520 --> 00:27:31.400 align:middle line:84%
And these people,
just like me, come

00:27:31.400 --> 00:27:33.860 align:middle line:84%
perhaps not consciously
knowing what

00:27:33.860 --> 00:27:36.300 align:middle line:90%
this pilgrimage is all about.

00:27:36.300 --> 00:27:39.896 align:middle line:84%
And yet I am told that we
will all receive the healing,

00:27:39.896 --> 00:27:42.940 align:middle line:84%
that all of this harmonized
and healed energy

00:27:42.940 --> 00:27:44.400 align:middle line:84%
is going to be for
the land to where

00:27:44.400 --> 00:27:48.206 align:middle line:84%
we came from, for our families,
and for our communities.

00:27:48.206 --> 00:27:51.790 align:middle line:90%


00:27:51.790 --> 00:27:53.980 align:middle line:84%
As we proceeded
down the mountains,

00:27:53.980 --> 00:27:55.930 align:middle line:84%
I mentioned to Puma
what Edemir had told

00:27:55.930 --> 00:27:59.875 align:middle line:90%
me about being from Atlantis.

00:27:59.875 --> 00:28:02.400 align:middle line:84%
He must have sensed
my disbelief.

00:28:02.400 --> 00:28:06.400 align:middle line:84%
Before I knew it,
12 hours later,

00:28:06.400 --> 00:28:09.280 align:middle line:90%
I found myself in Bolivia.

00:28:09.280 --> 00:28:14.390 align:middle line:84%
We'll be entering into what
is the realm of our ancestors.

00:28:14.390 --> 00:28:17.900 align:middle line:10%
Humanity before this one
were perhaps belonging

00:28:17.900 --> 00:28:19.920 align:middle line:10%
to the Atlantean civilizations.

00:28:19.920 --> 00:28:23.210 align:middle line:84%
And we'll be entering into
the mysteries of these people,

00:28:23.210 --> 00:28:26.750 align:middle line:84%
and what message they
left for these times

00:28:26.750 --> 00:28:28.700 align:middle line:90%
and for the humanity now.

00:28:28.700 --> 00:28:33.530 align:middle line:84%
They say that the era of
133 years before Christ

00:28:33.530 --> 00:28:38.570 align:middle line:84%
through 900 after Christ was the
best part of Tiwanaku culture.

00:28:38.570 --> 00:28:40.930 align:middle line:84%
And yet, this is only
the physical signs.

00:28:40.930 --> 00:28:44.860 align:middle line:84%
And knowing how limited it
has been in its research

00:28:44.860 --> 00:28:47.570 align:middle line:84%
and in its way of
finding out really,

00:28:47.570 --> 00:28:50.780 align:middle line:84%
this culture has developed
much more before that,

00:28:50.780 --> 00:28:53.670 align:middle line:84%
and its best times were
always at the beginning.

00:28:53.670 --> 00:28:56.960 align:middle line:84%
Because later, because of
weather or because of whatever

00:28:56.960 --> 00:29:00.980 align:middle line:84%
situations, this culture had
to also struggle to survive

00:29:00.980 --> 00:29:03.730 align:middle line:84%
and had to move to different
parts of the Andes.

00:29:03.730 --> 00:29:06.850 align:middle line:84%
And this is how the Inca
civilization even is born.

00:29:06.850 --> 00:29:09.370 align:middle line:84%
The origins of this
whole civilization

00:29:09.370 --> 00:29:12.470 align:middle line:84%
is here, in this
place, in this land.

00:29:12.470 --> 00:29:13.390 align:middle line:90%
This is the roots.

00:29:13.390 --> 00:29:14.720 align:middle line:90%
This is the source.

00:29:14.720 --> 00:29:18.050 align:middle line:84%
And like always in the
saying of the elders,

00:29:18.050 --> 00:29:20.480 align:middle line:84%
you must always remember
where you come from.

00:29:20.480 --> 00:29:23.770 align:middle line:84%
There's your power, there's your
roots, there's your strength.

00:29:23.770 --> 00:29:26.750 align:middle line:84%
And that is why we
are here in Tiwanaku.

00:29:26.750 --> 00:29:32.040 align:middle line:84%
And here we are in what they
call the underground temple.

00:29:32.040 --> 00:29:35.850 align:middle line:84%
This is the place where they
found the monolith of Bennett,

00:29:35.850 --> 00:29:36.550 align:middle line:90%
as they call it.

00:29:36.550 --> 00:29:38.710 align:middle line:90%
The monolith of Mother Earth.

00:29:38.710 --> 00:29:44.505 align:middle line:84%
But interestingly, all
the rocks extending out

00:29:44.505 --> 00:29:49.200 align:middle line:84%
represent the different
races of humanity.

00:29:49.200 --> 00:29:51.770 align:middle line:84%
This is basically
a temple dedicated

00:29:51.770 --> 00:29:54.240 align:middle line:90%
to the races of humanity.

00:29:54.240 --> 00:29:59.660 align:middle line:90%
Asian, African, everywhere.

00:29:59.660 --> 00:30:00.730 align:middle line:90%
Everywhere.

00:30:00.730 --> 00:30:01.720 align:middle line:90%
Everywhere.

00:30:01.720 --> 00:30:03.680 align:middle line:90%
You name one, it's here.

00:30:03.680 --> 00:30:06.620 align:middle line:90%


00:30:06.620 --> 00:30:11.140 align:middle line:84%
And the head represents where
our brain, where our mind is.

00:30:11.140 --> 00:30:18.300 align:middle line:84%
And knowing how limited,
knowing how rational are,

00:30:18.300 --> 00:30:20.050 align:middle line:84%
in these temples
is where they used

00:30:20.050 --> 00:30:25.660 align:middle line:84%
to heal the head of the whole
of humanity in our planet.

00:30:25.660 --> 00:30:27.390 align:middle line:84%
This is the place
where they would take

00:30:27.390 --> 00:30:30.250 align:middle line:84%
the limited mentality,
the rationality,

00:30:30.250 --> 00:30:32.890 align:middle line:90%
the making sense of everything.

00:30:32.890 --> 00:30:36.150 align:middle line:84%
They were able to heal
that here in this temple.

00:30:36.150 --> 00:30:38.960 align:middle line:84%
This is why I say
that healing does not

00:30:38.960 --> 00:30:41.410 align:middle line:90%
happen at an individual level.

00:30:41.410 --> 00:30:44.150 align:middle line:84%
Not only does it happen at
a family level and community

00:30:44.150 --> 00:30:47.300 align:middle line:84%
level, it happens in
temples like this,

00:30:47.300 --> 00:30:52.990 align:middle line:84%
happening to the level
of races of humanity.

00:30:52.990 --> 00:30:55.810 align:middle line:84%
That's at the level
we need to heal.

00:30:55.810 --> 00:30:57.660 align:middle line:90%
Globally.

00:30:57.660 --> 00:31:00.480 align:middle line:90%
PAM: A chill ran up my back.

00:31:00.480 --> 00:31:04.630 align:middle line:84%
Was this another
sign of recognition?

00:31:04.630 --> 00:31:07.470 align:middle line:84%
Puma explained that
sites such as this

00:31:07.470 --> 00:31:12.990 align:middle line:84%
were erected as actual doors or
portals used by our ancestors

00:31:12.990 --> 00:31:14.830 align:middle line:84%
to receive the knowledge
of the universe

00:31:14.830 --> 00:31:19.010 align:middle line:84%
directly from the heavens,
giving each of us that innate

00:31:19.010 --> 00:31:22.310 align:middle line:84%
wisdom, and connecting us
with the beings of light

00:31:22.310 --> 00:31:24.960 align:middle line:90%
from other galaxies.

00:31:24.960 --> 00:31:27.000 align:middle line:84%
Further down the
road, we entered

00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:28.590 align:middle line:90%
into a new archaeological dig.

00:31:28.590 --> 00:31:33.560 align:middle line:90%


00:31:33.560 --> 00:31:35.240 align:middle line:90%
PUMA: Puma Gate.

00:31:35.240 --> 00:31:38.840 align:middle line:84%
That is a recent name that
it had put to this place.

00:31:38.840 --> 00:31:41.700 align:middle line:10%
What we will appreciate
here in terms of symbols,

00:31:41.700 --> 00:31:47.900 align:middle line:10%
in terms of carvings, in terms
of highly advanced technology

00:31:47.900 --> 00:31:52.760 align:middle line:10%
in working with rock, belongs
to the Lemurian people

00:31:52.760 --> 00:31:55.690 align:middle line:10%
who were the ancestors
of the Atlanteans.

00:31:55.690 --> 00:31:58.660 align:middle line:10%
And because in the
Atlantean civilization

00:31:58.660 --> 00:32:02.090 align:middle line:10%
there were many events
happening where they broke

00:32:02.090 --> 00:32:05.190 align:middle line:10%
many cosmic laws, also
where they brought life

00:32:05.190 --> 00:32:09.350 align:middle line:10%
to an unbalance, that
way Mother Earth had

00:32:09.350 --> 00:32:11.730 align:middle line:10%
to use her four
elements in order

00:32:11.730 --> 00:32:15.250 align:middle line:10%
to purify and clean herself.

00:32:15.250 --> 00:32:17.570 align:middle line:84%
And with that, the
Atlantean civilization was

00:32:17.570 --> 00:32:20.020 align:middle line:90%
going to disappear completely.

00:32:20.020 --> 00:32:25.130 align:middle line:84%
And with that, also the
ancestry of the Lemurian people.

00:32:25.130 --> 00:32:29.590 align:middle line:84%
The Mu people were the
ancestors of the Atlanteans.

00:32:29.590 --> 00:32:36.430 align:middle line:84%
And because of the technology,
because of the magnitude

00:32:36.430 --> 00:32:43.630 align:middle line:84%
of carving and work in here
and of knowing all the laws

00:32:43.630 --> 00:32:48.260 align:middle line:84%
of the cosmos of
basically using levity

00:32:48.260 --> 00:32:53.785 align:middle line:84%
has the polarity of gravity and
taking the molecular weight out

00:32:53.785 --> 00:32:56.620 align:middle line:84%
of the rocks, such
technologies were

00:32:56.620 --> 00:32:58.360 align:middle line:90%
only known by these people.

00:32:58.360 --> 00:33:01.690 align:middle line:84%
And that is why, perhaps,
we called this Pumapunko

00:33:01.690 --> 00:33:03.340 align:middle line:90%
as the last Lemurian portal.

00:33:03.340 --> 00:33:09.680 align:middle line:90%


00:33:09.680 --> 00:33:12.390 align:middle line:90%
Everything is a portal.

00:33:12.390 --> 00:33:17.010 align:middle line:84%
This is a place that tells you
that your eyes are portals,

00:33:17.010 --> 00:33:19.520 align:middle line:84%
that your ear--
hearing is portals,

00:33:19.520 --> 00:33:21.800 align:middle line:90%
that your words are portals.

00:33:21.800 --> 00:33:24.235 align:middle line:84%
That your whole temple is a
portal, that your heart is

00:33:24.235 --> 00:33:26.880 align:middle line:84%
a portal, that
your belly button,

00:33:26.880 --> 00:33:31.950 align:middle line:84%
your navel is a portal, that
your sexual gland is a portal.

00:33:31.950 --> 00:33:36.140 align:middle line:84%
That you as a woman have a womb,
that there's a portal into.

00:33:36.140 --> 00:33:38.010 align:middle line:90%
Everything is portals.

00:33:38.010 --> 00:33:40.205 align:middle line:84%
And you choose to
be open or closed.

00:33:40.205 --> 00:33:43.590 align:middle line:90%


00:33:43.590 --> 00:33:48.210 align:middle line:84%
PAM: As we began our journey
back to Peru I asked Puma,

00:33:48.210 --> 00:33:49.800 align:middle line:84%
there are so many
people out there

00:33:49.800 --> 00:33:52.650 align:middle line:84%
representing themselves
as spiritual guides,

00:33:52.650 --> 00:33:54.660 align:middle line:90%
leaders of the path.

00:33:54.660 --> 00:34:00.630 align:middle line:84%
How do you recognize true
or false prophets, guides?

00:34:00.630 --> 00:34:03.390 align:middle line:84%
PUMA: While we're looking for
guides, while we're looking

00:34:03.390 --> 00:34:08.260 align:middle line:84%
for guidance, with
this intent that which

00:34:08.260 --> 00:34:12.070 align:middle line:84%
maintains us on the path,
which is the sacred fire.

00:34:12.070 --> 00:34:17.360 align:middle line:84%
Sacred fire that is in each
human being, in every person.

00:34:17.360 --> 00:34:21.600 align:middle line:84%
That besides their thinking,
besides their personality,

00:34:21.600 --> 00:34:25.439 align:middle line:84%
besides their way of being,
they are already that light.

00:34:25.439 --> 00:34:29.750 align:middle line:84%
They are already
that sacred spirit.

00:34:29.750 --> 00:34:32.489 align:middle line:84%
And when you look, when
you see at a person,

00:34:32.489 --> 00:34:34.020 align:middle line:90%
you see that sacred fire.

00:34:34.020 --> 00:34:37.880 align:middle line:84%
You see that love,
in spite of whatever

00:34:37.880 --> 00:34:41.239 align:middle line:90%
else is their appearance.

00:34:41.239 --> 00:34:43.850 align:middle line:84%
And you listen, and
you respect, and you

00:34:43.850 --> 00:34:45.840 align:middle line:90%
honor that being, that person.

00:34:45.840 --> 00:34:51.620 align:middle line:84%
Being on a path, being
in life with the process.

00:34:51.620 --> 00:34:54.380 align:middle line:90%
And you listen.

00:34:54.380 --> 00:34:57.020 align:middle line:84%
Because grandfather
would say, in the people

00:34:57.020 --> 00:35:02.480 align:middle line:84%
that you less think of, there
is where your teachers are.

00:35:02.480 --> 00:35:04.100 align:middle line:90%
There is where your guides are.

00:35:04.100 --> 00:35:05.950 align:middle line:90%
So you don't look for them.

00:35:05.950 --> 00:35:08.100 align:middle line:90%
They will find you.

00:35:08.100 --> 00:35:10.780 align:middle line:84%
PAM: As we left Bolivia,
I mentioned to Puma

00:35:10.780 --> 00:35:13.180 align:middle line:84%
that I had overheard
some of my travel mates

00:35:13.180 --> 00:35:16.940 align:middle line:84%
talk about the end of the
Mayan calendar in 2012,

00:35:16.940 --> 00:35:20.680 align:middle line:84%
and the subsequent destruction
of earth as we know it.

00:35:20.680 --> 00:35:24.220 align:middle line:84%
As we waited for the bus,
Puma explained this in terms

00:35:24.220 --> 00:35:26.170 align:middle line:90%
used by the Quechua elders.

00:35:26.170 --> 00:35:29.530 align:middle line:84%
PUMA: We have here what
we call a taripay pacha,

00:35:29.530 --> 00:35:34.660 align:middle line:84%
a time in which we're entering
into a major transition

00:35:34.660 --> 00:35:36.130 align:middle line:90%
as humanity.

00:35:36.130 --> 00:35:39.530 align:middle line:84%
And Mother Earth will
allow a lot of our healing

00:35:39.530 --> 00:35:44.250 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of our spiritual
growth and awakening

00:35:44.250 --> 00:35:45.650 align:middle line:90%
in this transition.

00:35:45.650 --> 00:35:50.420 align:middle line:10%
We call it first
there is pachacuti.

00:35:50.420 --> 00:35:55.890 align:middle line:10%
Pachacuti is a time and space.

00:35:55.890 --> 00:36:03.100 align:middle line:84%
Ancient energies, ancient
wisdom, ancient knowledge,

00:36:03.100 --> 00:36:08.150 align:middle line:84%
ancestors coming back
and reorganizing.

00:36:08.150 --> 00:36:12.560 align:middle line:84%
Helping us wake up, helping
us heal, helping us transform.

00:36:12.560 --> 00:36:14.920 align:middle line:84%
That is what we
call a pachacuti.

00:36:14.920 --> 00:36:19.450 align:middle line:10%
In the process, we have to
go through a taripay pacha.

00:36:19.450 --> 00:36:22.710 align:middle line:10%
Taripay pacha
means not a new way

00:36:22.710 --> 00:36:27.850 align:middle line:10%
of life, not new steps in life.

00:36:27.850 --> 00:36:34.340 align:middle line:84%
But rather that time and space
will catch up with our growth.

00:36:34.340 --> 00:36:37.570 align:middle line:84%
Meaning the eternal
knowledge, the eternal wisdom,

00:36:37.570 --> 00:36:41.170 align:middle line:84%
and the eternal
consciousness will again

00:36:41.170 --> 00:36:43.450 align:middle line:90%
be integrated into our lives.

00:36:43.450 --> 00:36:45.680 align:middle line:84%
And that will
allow our awakening

00:36:45.680 --> 00:36:49.300 align:middle line:84%
and our transformation in
this moment of transition

00:36:49.300 --> 00:36:51.080 align:middle line:84%
that Mother Earth
is going through,

00:36:51.080 --> 00:36:55.080 align:middle line:84%
which will also affect the whole
cosmos and the whole universe.

00:36:55.080 --> 00:36:58.560 align:middle line:84%
So the taripay pacha
is for all of us

00:36:58.560 --> 00:37:03.150 align:middle line:84%
to become the elders, for all
of us to become the wise ones,

00:37:03.150 --> 00:37:09.730 align:middle line:84%
for all of us to become
the healers, the leaders.

00:37:09.730 --> 00:37:13.562 align:middle line:10%
PAM: Once back in Peru, our
first stop was in Cusco, where

00:37:13.562 --> 00:37:16.000 align:middle line:10%
I received a follow-up
from my ankle injury,

00:37:16.000 --> 00:37:21.250 align:middle line:10%
and I was introduced to
Mother Irene, a local healer.

00:37:21.250 --> 00:37:23.150 align:middle line:84%
PUMA: This little
baby got burned three

00:37:23.150 --> 00:37:25.900 align:middle line:90%
days ago with very hot stuff.

00:37:25.900 --> 00:37:27.360 align:middle line:90%
So he's back.

00:37:27.360 --> 00:37:28.900 align:middle line:90%
He's hurt.

00:37:28.900 --> 00:37:31.754 align:middle line:90%
But they're going to heal.

00:37:31.754 --> 00:37:34.770 align:middle line:90%
[BABY CRYING]

00:37:34.770 --> 00:37:38.550 align:middle line:84%
Whenever children have
these problems, what

00:37:38.550 --> 00:37:40.670 align:middle line:84%
they need healing for
is not only the body,

00:37:40.670 --> 00:37:44.470 align:middle line:90%
but also for the spirit.

00:37:44.470 --> 00:37:49.360 align:middle line:84%
So they're taking care of the
energetic part of the baby.

00:37:49.360 --> 00:37:52.690 align:middle line:90%
They will be healing its spirit.

00:37:52.690 --> 00:37:57.200 align:middle line:84%
And whatever traumas or
whatever fear that the baby has

00:37:57.200 --> 00:37:58.980 align:middle line:90%
will be liberated and cleansed.

00:37:58.980 --> 00:38:01.640 align:middle line:90%


00:38:01.640 --> 00:38:04.270 align:middle line:84%
In three days, you
could see how the body

00:38:04.270 --> 00:38:06.360 align:middle line:90%
has recuperated so fast.

00:38:06.360 --> 00:38:09.390 align:middle line:90%
Because they use natural herbs.

00:38:09.390 --> 00:38:11.850 align:middle line:84%
Irene has everything
prepared ready.

00:38:11.850 --> 00:38:14.090 align:middle line:84%
PAM: And this was a burn from
the fireplace from an oven,

00:38:14.090 --> 00:38:14.790 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:38:14.790 --> 00:38:15.490 align:middle line:90%
PUMA: Yeah.

00:38:15.490 --> 00:38:18.800 align:middle line:84%
But the physical part is not
the most important, you see?

00:38:18.800 --> 00:38:20.000 align:middle line:84%
A lot of these
children, when they

00:38:20.000 --> 00:38:24.170 align:middle line:84%
go through these experiences,
they catch a very strong trauma

00:38:24.170 --> 00:38:27.050 align:middle line:84%
because their psychological
temple is 10 times more

00:38:27.050 --> 00:38:29.780 align:middle line:84%
vulnerable than
ours as an adult.

00:38:29.780 --> 00:38:33.500 align:middle line:84%
So it is important to heal the
emotional and the spiritual

00:38:33.500 --> 00:38:35.590 align:middle line:84%
part also, because
that is going to affect

00:38:35.590 --> 00:38:38.215 align:middle line:84%
the rest of their lives,
even when they become adults.

00:38:38.215 --> 00:38:41.100 align:middle line:90%


00:38:41.100 --> 00:38:43.180 align:middle line:84%
The same thing's
happening to the baby

00:38:43.180 --> 00:38:46.760 align:middle line:84%
over there too, because
he fell down on the steps.

00:38:46.760 --> 00:38:48.330 align:middle line:84%
And so they're
trying to heal all

00:38:48.330 --> 00:38:50.140 align:middle line:90%
the trauma that he might have.

00:38:50.140 --> 00:38:55.350 align:middle line:90%


00:38:55.350 --> 00:38:57.640 align:middle line:84%
Notice how the
child is completely

00:38:57.640 --> 00:39:00.760 align:middle line:84%
focused, and
receives the healing.

00:39:00.760 --> 00:39:05.532 align:middle line:84%
Because they learn from very
young that this is important.

00:39:05.532 --> 00:39:09.404 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:39:09.404 --> 00:39:11.824 align:middle line:90%


00:39:11.824 --> 00:39:13.276 align:middle line:90%
PUMA: OK.

00:39:13.276 --> 00:39:17.680 align:middle line:84%
And you can see at the end, she
will do a reading in the water,

00:39:17.680 --> 00:39:20.670 align:middle line:84%
which is sort of like an oracle,
about how each person is,

00:39:20.670 --> 00:39:21.604 align:middle line:90%
how each baby is.

00:39:21.604 --> 00:39:27.680 align:middle line:90%


00:39:27.680 --> 00:39:30.960 align:middle line:84%
We have the sacred plants,
the medicinal plants.

00:39:30.960 --> 00:39:34.390 align:middle line:84%
Just like we have each
one of us a specific gift,

00:39:34.390 --> 00:39:36.510 align:middle line:84%
whether it is in our
knowledge, whether it

00:39:36.510 --> 00:39:39.670 align:middle line:84%
is in our activities, whether
it's in something we do.

00:39:39.670 --> 00:39:43.560 align:middle line:84%
Same way plants also have
a specific gift for us.

00:39:43.560 --> 00:39:49.770 align:middle line:84%
And for centuries, our ancestors
have been working with them,

00:39:49.770 --> 00:39:52.060 align:middle line:84%
and have been using
them for healing

00:39:52.060 --> 00:39:53.380 align:middle line:90%
in various different ways.

00:39:53.380 --> 00:39:55.450 align:middle line:84%
One thing I have learned
about medicinal plants

00:39:55.450 --> 00:39:59.590 align:middle line:84%
from my grandmother is that
there's a whole family of them.

00:39:59.590 --> 00:40:03.500 align:middle line:84%
You must recognize the
grandmother plants,

00:40:03.500 --> 00:40:07.520 align:middle line:84%
the grandfather plants, the
parents, and the children,

00:40:07.520 --> 00:40:09.760 align:middle line:90%
and the grandchildren.

00:40:09.760 --> 00:40:13.120 align:middle line:84%
For example, the ancestral
plans or the elder plants

00:40:13.120 --> 00:40:18.250 align:middle line:84%
would be like Wachuma as
they know it as San Pedro

00:40:18.250 --> 00:40:22.470 align:middle line:90%
or Ayahusca, or [INAUDIBLE].

00:40:22.470 --> 00:40:25.910 align:middle line:84%
All these master
plants that we used

00:40:25.910 --> 00:40:31.220 align:middle line:84%
only in a very sacred way
for the deepest awakening.

00:40:31.220 --> 00:40:34.590 align:middle line:84%
And the other
plants, the parents,

00:40:34.590 --> 00:40:37.110 align:middle line:84%
would be the ones that
are important if you

00:40:37.110 --> 00:40:40.170 align:middle line:84%
have infections, if
you have inflammation.

00:40:40.170 --> 00:40:42.870 align:middle line:84%
But you also use
them internally.

00:40:42.870 --> 00:40:46.930 align:middle line:84%
And some of the younger
plants are the ones

00:40:46.930 --> 00:40:48.700 align:middle line:90%
that you use externally.

00:40:48.700 --> 00:40:52.210 align:middle line:84%
Instead of an antibiotic, you
could use some of these plants.

00:40:52.210 --> 00:40:55.970 align:middle line:84%
And the other medicine
are new plants.

00:40:55.970 --> 00:40:58.020 align:middle line:84%
New plants, the children
plants, are the ones

00:40:58.020 --> 00:41:03.630 align:middle line:84%
that you could use them in tea
every day if it's good for you.

00:41:03.630 --> 00:41:07.940 align:middle line:90%
Or you could use them in baths.

00:41:07.940 --> 00:41:10.650 align:middle line:84%
You could put them
in the specific pots

00:41:10.650 --> 00:41:12.840 align:middle line:90%
and bathe with them.

00:41:12.840 --> 00:41:15.830 align:middle line:84%
These plans are at the level
that they give themselves

00:41:15.830 --> 00:41:19.710 align:middle line:84%
completely in service
for our well being,

00:41:19.710 --> 00:41:23.940 align:middle line:84%
for our being balanced and
for our being in good health,

00:41:23.940 --> 00:41:26.860 align:middle line:84%
and for us being
in life connected

00:41:26.860 --> 00:41:29.150 align:middle line:90%
and grounded and happy.

00:41:29.150 --> 00:41:32.150 align:middle line:84%
So that is why medicinal
plants are a very important

00:41:32.150 --> 00:41:33.555 align:middle line:90%
part of our healing also.

00:41:33.555 --> 00:41:36.285 align:middle line:90%


00:41:36.285 --> 00:41:38.134 align:middle line:84%
PAM: It starts feeling
better the more you do it.

